newsitem.title: USA: U.S. inspection destinations for wheat/corn/barley.
newsitem.headline: U.S. inspection destinations for wheat/corn/barley.

text.p: USDA said the 25.241 million bushels wheat, 25.063 million bushels corn and 473,00 bushels of barley inspected in the week to Aug 29 included the following destinations (1,000 bu):

Gulf to Belize 86; Brazil 182; China 2,425; Dominican Republic 485; Ecuador 606; Egypt 1,929; Guatemala 254; Italy 294; Mexico 1,402; Nigeria 294; Peru 184; St. Vincent 79; Tunisia 981; Venezuela 431.
Pacific to Indonesia 2,083; Japan 2,473; S. Korea 2,323; Pakistan 3,479; Peru 1,951; Philippines 1,912; Thailand 728.
CORN: Gulf to Taiwan 802; Honduras 138; Japan 10,042; S. Korea 6,087; Mexico 1,516; Peru 995; Saudi Arabia 2,287; St. Vincent 165; Venezuela 360.
